{"ts":"2026-07-13T19:55:47.329Z","author":"codex-root","op":"learning_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-13T19:55:47.329Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-13T19:55:47.329Z","author":"codex-root","text":"A token-bounded selector needs two separate completeness concepts: projection completeness (everything fit at full detail) and search completeness (the latency budget allowed every candidate comparison). Disclosing both prevents a fast degraded packet from masquerading as an exact optimum."}]}],"before_hash":"cfc52b59deb3ed810a320b180bb1eb02be318ae97a25a62100eb7c125162116c","after_hash":"edfd2c27f0d15b6ecb8479db7abc398240ab8f486bf9c735387d26b93cb449b1","message":"Record packer design learning"}
